Add several fields into an array containing objects

I am trying to update an object into an array in MongoDB.
Here are my documents :

> db.devis.insert({id:1,obj:[{'code':'A'},{'code':'B'}]})  
> db.devis.insert({id:2,obj:[{'code':'C'},{'code':'D'}]})  

> db.devis.find()
[
  {
    id: 1,
    obj: [ { code: 'A' }, { code: 'B' } ]
  },
  {
    id: 2,
    obj: [ { code: 'C'}, { code: 'D' } ]
  }

  obj: [ { code: 'A'}, { code: 'B', a: 'a'} ]

Now I want to add several fields :

  id: 1,
  obj: [ { code: 'A'}, { foo: 'foo', bar: 'bar'} ]
}

# What I want
{
  id: 1,
  obj: [ { code: 'A'}, { code: 'B', foo: 'foo', bar: 'bar'} ]
}

embedfield:
MongoDB: Sorting, subtracting dates and counting

I'm a begginer in MongoDB and I'm practising the aggregation method. I'm my example, I would like to get the wine which has been produced in the last 5 years (5 years back from the newest wine), then I would like to count how many wines have been produced in that period of time (the database gives us the year of the wines, in an integer)

I believe that first, I have to sort the wines by year, then I should get the year of the newest wine, and sustract five years, using that period of time to count the wines. But I don't know how to write all of that using the aggregation code.

Thanks!
answer: @Jeroen : I hate to say this, but your theories are completely incorrect. First of all his method doesn't include any parameters, so this has nothing to do with `ByVal` nor `ByRef`. And it doesn't matter if he calls another method because it'd still be the same as doing it directly. Secondly a `ListBox` _is a reference type_ (a class) meaning you will always get it by reference.

I believe that first, I have to sort the wines by year, then I should get the year of the newest wine, and sustract five years, using that period of time to count the wines. But I don't know how to write all of that using the aggregation code.

Secondly a `ListBox` _is a reference type_ (a class) meaning you will always get it by reference.
